{"repo": "Flexget/Flexget", "pull_number": 4954, "instance_id": "Flexget__Flexget-4954", "issue_numbers": [4953], "base_commit": "a88c9d72efabea7400369beef5dc7cd971fcb815", "patch": "diff --git a/flexget/ipc.py b/flexget/ipc.py\nindex 69421b0910..695eced410 100644\n--- a/flexget/ipc.py\n+++ b/flexget/ipc.py\n@@ -2,12 +2,14 @@\n \n import contextlib\n import logging\n+import os\n import random\n import string\n import threading\n import unittest.mock\n from typing import TYPE_CHECKING\n \n+import rich.text\n import rpyc\n from loguru import logger\n from rpyc.utils.server import ThreadedServer\n@@ -73,14 +75,15 @@ def exposed_version(self):\n     def exposed_handle_cli(self, args):\n         args = rpyc.utils.classic.obtain(args)\n         logger.verbose('Running command `{}` for client.', ' '.join(args))\n-        parser = get_parser()\n-        try:\n-            options = parser.parse_args(args, file=self.client_out_stream)\n-        except SystemExit as e:\n-            if e.code:\n-                # TODO: Not sure how to properly propagate the exit code back to client\n-                logger.debug('Parsing cli args caused system exit with status {}.', e.code)\n-            return\n+        with unittest.mock.patch.dict(os.environ, {'FORCE_COLOR': '1'}):\n+            parser = get_parser()\n+            try:\n+                options = parser.parse_args(args, file=self.client_out_stream)\n+            except SystemExit as e:\n+                if e.code:\n+                    # TODO: Not sure how to properly propagate the exit code back to client\n+                    logger.debug('Parsing cli args caused system exit with status {}.', e.code)\n+                return\n         context_managers = []\n         # Don't capture any output when used with --cron\n         if not options.cron:\n@@ -99,7 +102,7 @@ def exposed_handle_cli(self, args):\n \n     @property\n     def client_out_stream(self):\n-        return RemoteStream(self._conn.root.console)\n+        return RemoteStream(self._conn.root.write)\n \n     def client_log_sink(self, message):\n         return self._conn.root.log_sink(message)\n@@ -122,6 +125,11 @@ def exposed_console(self, text, *args, **kwargs):\n         text = rpyc.classic.obtain(text)\n         terminal.console(text, *args, **kwargs)\n \n+    def exposed_write(self, text, *args, **kwargs):\n+        text = rpyc.classic.obtain(text)\n+        text = rich.text.Text.from_ansi(text)\n+        terminal.console(text, *args, **kwargs)\n+\n     def exposed_log_sink(self, message):\n         message = rpyc.classic.obtain(message)\n         record = message.record\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Broken ANSI escapes when daemon is running\n### Summary\n\nWhen flexget is running as daemon, other invocations of flexget will receive text with broken ANSI escapes.\n\n### Minimal reproducible config\n\n```yaml\n1. `flexget daemon start`\n2. Open another terminal, run `flexget -h`\n```\n\n### Log\n\n```text\nThere is a FlexGet process already running for this config, sending execution there.\n[1;34musage: [0m[1;35mflexget[0m [[32m-V[0m] [[36m--test[0m] [[32m-c [33mCONFIG[0m] [[36m--logfile\n[33mLOGFILE[0m] [[36m--loglevel [33mLEVEL[0m] [[36m--profile [33m[OUTFILE][0m]\n               [[36m--cron[0m] [[36m--help[0m] [[36m--debug-db-sessions[0m] [[36m--debug-warnings[0m]\n               [32m<command> ...[0m\n\n[1;34moptions:[0m\n  [1;32m-V[0m, [1;36m--version[0m         Print FlexGet version and exit.\n  [1;36m--test[0m                Verbose what would happen on normal execution.\n  [1;32m-c[0m [1;33mCONFIG[0m             Specify configuration file. Default: config.yml\n  [1;36m--logfile[0m, [1;32m-l[0m [1;33mLOGFILE[0m\n                        Specify a custom logfile name/location. Default: flexget.log in the config\n                        directory.\n  [1;36m--loglevel[0m, [1;32m-L[0m [1;33mLEVEL[0m  Set the verbosity of the logger. Levels: NONE, CRITICAL,\nERROR, WARNING, INFO,\n                        VERBOSE, DEBUG, TRACE\n  [1;36m--profile[0m [1;33m[OUTFILE][0m   Use the python profiler for this run to debug performance issues.\n  [1;36m--cron[0m                use when executing FlexGet non-interactively: allows background\nmaintenance to\n                        run, disables stdout and stderr output, reduces logging level\n  [1;36m--help[0m, [1;32m-h[0m            Show this help message and exit\n  [1;36m--debug-db-sessions[0m   debug session starts and ends, for finding problems with db locks\n  [1;36m--debug-warnings[0m      elevate warnings to errors for debugging purposes, so a traceback is shown\n\n[1;34mcommands:[0m\n  [1;32m<command>[0m\n    [1;32mexecute[0m             execute tasks now\n    [1;32mdaemon[0m              run continuously, executing tasks according to schedules defined in config\n    [1;32mexport-schema[0m       Output the JSON schema for the config\n    [1;32mweb[0m                 Manage web server settings\n    [1;32mdatabase[0m            Utilities to manage the FlexGet database\n    [1;32mplugins[0m             Print registered plugin summaries\n    [1;32mcheck[0m               validate configuration file and print errors\n    [1;32mdebug-info[0m          display useful info for debugging\n    [1;32mtemplates[0m           View all available templates\n    [1;32mdoc[0m                 display plugin documentation\n    [1;32mjinja-filters[0m       View registered jinja2 filters and their description\n    [1;32mtorznab[0m             Query torznab indexer capabilities\n    [1;32mirc[0m                 View and manage irc connections\n    [1;32mbacklog[0m             View or clear entries from backlog plugin\n    [1;32mseen[0m                View or forget entries remembered by the seen plugin\n    [1;32mhistory[0m             View the history of entries that FlexGet has accepted\n    [1;32marchive[0m             Search and manipulate the archive database\n    [1;32mpending[0m             View and manage pending entries\n    [1;32mtrakt[0m               View and manage trakt authentication.\n    [1;32mfailed[0m              list or clear remembered failures\n    [1;32mrejected[0m            list or clear remembered rejections\n    [1;32mstatus[0m              View task health status\n    [1;32mseries[0m              View and manipulate the series plugin database\n    [1;32mregexp-list[0m         View and manage regexp lists\n    [1;32mmovie-list[0m          View and manage movie lists\n    [1;32mpending-list[0m        View and manage pending lists\n    [1;32mentry-list[0m          view and manage entry lists\n    [1;32minject[0m              inject an entry from command line into tasks\n```\n\n### Additional information\n\n**FlexGet Version:** 3.19.8\n**Python Version:** 3.14.3\n**OS Version:** Arch Linux x86_64, Linux 6.19.9-arch1-1\n**Installation Method:** pipx or git clone\n**Using Daemon (yes/no):** yes\n", "hints_text": "Running through `script -c flexget -h` gives the following output:\n<details>\n<summary>cat -v typescript</summary>\n\n```\nScript started on 2026-03-31 01:56:04+02:00 [COMMAND=\"./flexget_vanilla.py -c config.yml -h\" TERM=\"alacritty\" TTY=\"/dev/pts/2\" COLUMNS=\"-1\" LINES=\"-1\"]\nThere is a FlexGet process already running for this config, sending execution there.^M\n^[^[[1m[^[[0m^[[1;36m1^[[0m;34musage: ^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m^[^[[1m[^[[0m^[[1;36m1^[[0m;35mflexget^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m ^[[1m[^[[0m^[^[[1m[^[[0m32m-V^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m^[[1m]^[[0m ^[[1m[^[[0m^[^[[1m[^[[0m36m--test^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m^[[1m]^[[0m ^[[1m[^[[0m^[^[[1m[^[[0m32m-c ^[^[[1m[^[[0m33mCONFIG^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m^[[1m]^[[0m ^[[1m[^[[0m^[^[[1m[^[[0m36m--logfile^M\n^[^[[1m[^[[0m33mLOGFILE^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m^[[1m]^[[0m^M\n               ^[[1m[^[[0m^[^[[1m[^[[0m36m--loglevel ^[^[[1m[^[[0m33mLEVEL^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m^[[1m]^[[0m ^[[1m[^[[0m^[^[[1m[^[[0m36m--profile ^[^[[1m[^[[0m33m^[[1m[^[[0mOUTFILE^[[1m]^[[0m^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m^[[1m]^[[0m ^[[1m[^[[0m^[^[[1m[^[[0m36m--cron^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m^[[1m]^[[0m ^M\n^[[1m[^[[0m^[^[[1m[^[[0m36m--help^[^[[1m[^[[