gin database^M\n    ^[^[[1m[^[[0m^[[1;36m1^[[0m;32mregexp-list^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m         View and manage regexp lists^M\n    ^[^[[1m[^[[0m^[[1;36m1^[[0m;32mmovie-list^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m          View and manage movie lists^M\n    ^[^[[1m[^[[0m^[[1;36m1^[[0m;32mpending-list^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m        View and manage pending lists^M\n    ^[^[[1m[^[[0m^[[1;36m1^[[0m;32mentry-list^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m          view and manage entry lists^M\n    ^[^[[1m[^[[0m^[[1;36m1^[[0m;32minject^[^[[1m[^[[0m0m              inject an entry from command line into tasks^M\n\nScript done on 2026-03-31 01:56:04+02:00 [COMMAND_EXIT_CODE=\"0\"]\n```\n\n</details>\n\nIt appears to be double escaping. So `cat typescript | sed 's/\\x1b\\[[0-9;]*m//g'` indeed produces the correct colored output.\n<details>\n<summary>Stripping one layer of ANSI escapes</summary>\n<img width=\"1213\" height=\"1403\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2fa075e7-1554-4459-86c7-22e6a97294c7\" />\n</details>\nI realized this only happens to `--help` outputs. And the culprit is probably\nhttps://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/blob/a88c9d72efabea7400369beef5dc7cd971fcb815/flexget/ipc.py#L78-L102\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/commit/1cb0a6762f40ae58993ebdceccf290343342f3c8", "https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/commit/2fd69ec9fdd80dc5e19e9253eade1f5d3e792dee"], "created_at": "2026-03-31T07:21:20Z"}
